FT  23 MAR 93 / Parliament and Politics: Anticipated job losses as result of
council budget cuts reach 34,643
Mr Jack Straw, Labour's local government spokesman, yesterday claimed that
anticipated job losses as a result of council budget cuts have now reached
34,643 since February. Mr Straw (above left) with Mr Frank Dobson, the
shadow employment spokesman, said monitoring by the Centre for Local
Economic Strategies had also shown a 'knock-on' effect from the cuts hitting
employment in the private sector. Mr Robin Squire, the environment minister,
replied that many of the 'losses' could be attributed to contracting-out of
services
